We are trying to write swerve code with phoenix tuner x, however when we try to configurate our motors like FL, it gives 2 error messages.

Average Encoder (vel: 0) or Steer Motor (vel: 0) velocities were below threshold. If the module correctly moved, verify the selected CANcoder is the correct CANcoder by blinking it.

and

Drive Motor (vel: 0) velocities were below threshold. Verify the drive motors moved and the robot was enabled.

We checked a few posts which were talking about the same problem we have but they didn’t solve our problem.
